# WordPress Theme Architecture

- Theme init: [functions.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/functions.php) configures TailPress, registers assets (Vite compiler), theme supports, and menus (`primary`).
- Rendering flow:
  - [index.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/index.php) is the primary template; it handles archive/singular contexts and loads template parts.
  - Template part for single: [template-parts/content-single.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/template-parts/content-single.php)
  - Header/Footer wrappers: [header.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/header.php), [footer.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/footer.php)
- Utilities/components live under [src/](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/src) (e.g., [src/Pagination.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/src/Pagination.php)). Use namespaced static helpers from templates.
- Global design tokens and editor settings: [theme.json](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/theme.json).
- Register menus via TailPress `features/menus` in [functions.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/functions.php); render with `wp_nav_menu` (see [header.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/header.php)).
- Prefer TailPress asset registration rather than manual enqueues to keep Vite/Tailwind integration consistent.
